For the potato cakes, place the mashed potato into a bowl with the cheese, flour and egg and mix well. Season with salt and freshly ground black pepper, then shape the mixture into three patties.Heat the oil and butter in a frying pan and fry the potato cakes for 3-4 minutes on each side, or until golden-brown.For the tomato salsa, place all of the salsa ingredients into a bowl and stir to combine.To serve, place the potato cakes onto a serving plate with the crisp parma ham and poached egg on top and the salsa spooned around the plate.